          "page": 19,
          "source_pdf": "TMUA 2022 Paper 2(4).pdf"
        },
        "content": {
          "subject": "math",
          "topic": "proof_and_logic",
          "subtopic": null,
          "archetype": null,
          "difficulty": 4,
          "requires_diagram": false,
          "requires_calculation": false
        },
        "prompt": {
          "stem": "A student answered the following question:\n\n$a$ and $b$ are non-zero real numbers.\n\nProve that the equation $x^3 + ax^2 + b = 0$ has three distinct real roots if\n$27b\\\\left(b + \\frac{4a^3}{27}\\\\right) < 0$\n\nHere is the student’s solution:\n\nI     We differentiate $y = x^3 + ax^2 + b$ to get\n$\\\\dfrac{dy}{dx} = 3x^2 + 2ax = x(3x + 2a)$\n      Solving $\\dfrac{dy}{dx} = 0$ shows that the stationary points are at $(0,b)$ and\n$\\\\left(-\\\\frac{2a}{3}, b + \\\\frac{4a^3}{27}\\\\right)$\n\nII    If $27b\\\\left(b + \\\\frac{4a^3}{27}\\\\right) < 0$, then $b$ and $b + \\\\frac{4a^3}{27}$ must have opposite signs, and so one of\n      the stationary points is above the $x$-axis and one is below.\n\nIII   If the cubic has three distinct real roots, then one of the stationary points is above the\n      $x$-axis and one is below.\n\nIV    Hence if $27b\\\\left(b + \\\\frac{4a^3}{27}\\\\right) < 0$, then the equation has three distinct real roots.\n\nWhich one of the following options best describes the student’s solution?",
          "options": [
            {
              "label": "A",
              "text": "It is a completely correct solution."
            },
            {
              "label": "B",
              "text": "The student has instead proved the converse of the statement in the question."
            },
            {
              "label": "C",
              "text": "The solution is wrong, because the student should have stated step II after step III."
            },
            {
              "label": "D",
              "text": "The solution is wrong, because the student should have shown the converse of the result in step II."
            },
            {
              "label": "E",
              "text": "The solution is wrong, because the student should have shown the converse of the result in step III."
            }
          ],
          "figures": []
